00:06:30,029 --> 00:06:34,031
But before I go into those, I want to tell you the real reasons, the unofficial reasons.

115
00:06:34,912 --> 00:06:38,655
I just thought it would be really fun to take a game that I'd already made elsewhere

116
00:06:39,015 --> 00:06:44,721
and then bring it onto Steam with all the challenges and all the cool things that could be done with it.

117
00:06:45,141 --> 00:06:51,867
I'm a PC gamer at heart and there was a certain appeal to being able to take the baby that I'd created and then put it on the platform.

118
00:06:52,207 --> 00:06:55,129
that started me off on my love for games.

119
00:06:55,509 --> 00:06:57,109
So I already really wanted to do it,

120
00:06:57,169 --> 00:06:59,670
and the game designer in me also was sort of

121
00:06:59,911 --> 00:07:01,631
leaping at this chance to be able to

122
00:07:01,891 --> 00:07:04,152
take my big list of stuff that I hadn't been able

123
00:07:04,172 --> 00:07:05,373
to put in the game initially,

124
00:07:05,713 --> 00:07:08,754
and then make it, realize these through Steam.

125
00:07:08,774 --> 00:07:11,235
I only did about 50% of my design documents.

